\subsection{Procedures}
Study 1a participants completed a Qualtrics survey in which they were pseudo-randomly assigned to view 12 out of the 140 stimuli so that stimuli were shown evenly across participants. After viewing each stimulus, participants rated their current urge to drink alcohol, followed by their emotional responses to the stimulus, followed by their perceptions of the source of the stimulus, the perceived valence of the stimulus, and familiarity with the portrayed scene. Each stimulus was rated by an average of $\Sexpr{round(s$m,2)}$ (SD = $\Sexpr{round(s$s,2)}$) participants.

